title: Kaatsen at the 1928 Summer Olympics
text:
<a href="Kaatsen">Kaatsen</a> or Frisian handball (; ) was featured in the <a href="1928%20Summer%20Olympics">1928 Summer Olympics</a> unofficial programme.
Kaatsen is a traditional <a href="Friesland">Frisian</a> sport, related to <a href="American%20handball">American handball</a> and <a href="fives">fives</a>, that is most commonly practiced by people from the northern Dutch province of <a href="Friesland">Friesland</a> ("Fryslân"). It is believed to be one of the oldest ballgames. The score is similar to tennis. The first team scoring six games wins the match.
